element.name: Data Ingestion
element.documentation: FEMADex data-ingestion capabilities will enable users to transport data from FEMA source systems to multiple FEMADex single data lakes, where they will be able to access, use, and analyze the data.

element.name: Data Integration
element.documentation: FEMADex data-integration capabilities will enable users to combine data from disparate source systems through a combination of technical and FEMA business processes. Through integration, data will be able to be transformed into meaningful information that will then serve as the foundation for the next step in the data-analytics pipeline.

element.name: Data Transformation
element.documentation: FEMADex users will be able to transform the integrated data from the previous step and use it in an array of business processes. Examples of data-transformation activities include using data to make comparisons with other data sets, converting data types, removing duplicated data, aggregating data using formulas, and formatting data for a specific presentation.

element.name: Data Visualization
element.documentation: FEMADex users will be able to communicate insights from data through visual representations of large data sets in graphics to make complex relationships among the data easier to understand.

element.name: Data Governance and Management
element.documentation: This capability enforces data governance and management policies or provides tools for FEMA programs Data Stewards to adopt them.

element.name: Data Storage
element.documentation: This capability allows raw datasets from source systems to be stored before getting processed and transformed through the analytic pipeline.

element.name: Data Dissemination
element.documentation: FEMADex users will be able to publish transformed data to other users in various formats.

element.name: Private Data Exchange
element.documentation: FEMADex Private Data Exchange capabilities will enable analytical products created through the sharing process to External Partners, such as the American Red Cross, the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), and the U.S. Census Bureau.

element.name: Public Data Space
element.documentation: FEMADexâ€™s Public Data Space will provide a one-way path for publishing publicly qualified data and making it accessible to the general public.

element.name: User Portal
element.documentation: The User Portal will provide a starting point for a multiple users and purposes to allow them to access different capabilities within FEMADex.

element.name: Help Desk Portal
element.documentation: The Help Desk Portal, which will be integrated with the existing FEMA Enterprise Service Desk (ESD) Portal, will enable users to find answers to questions they may have about FEMADex using supportive resources such as Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs), User Guides, and Contact Information.

element.name: Training Portal
element.documentation: The Training Portal will enable users to practice their tasks on FEMADex tools to create analytical products. It will house information about analytical products, code, and process instructions to solve specific problems associated with events that either have occurred or may occur in the future.

element.name: Cost Management Portal
element.documentation: The Cost Management Portal will aggregate the costs associated with multiple CSPs and on-premises software licensing into a single view, enabling users to view the total cost of the system.
